Hi Martin,


The model shown in the print output and forest plot of metainf() depends 
on the model you have specified in the meta-analysis. Thus if you want 
to see the sensitivity plot for the random effects model, you have to 
set random = TRUE in the metaprop() command.


Note that the name of the arguments have changed with the most recent 
version 5.0-0 of meta:

comb.fixed -> fixed

comb.random -> random


Best,

Gerta


