Luke,

As a starting point, I would suggest creating graphs across _all_ of
the control groups, just treating every group as a data point and
ignoring the nesting structure. Sure, there might be some nuance to
the over-time relation within studies versus the between-study
relations. But as a first step, I think it would be reasonable to just
look at the mean-variance relationships across the whole dataset.

James

